Where can we install NEVI corridor chargers?

library(readxl)
library(ggplot2)
library(sf)
library(readr)

This is a map of the publicly available DC fast chargers across California. Almost all of them fit into the Corrodor Charger criteria (Within 1 mile from a highway). The buffer aroud the charger stations indicate a radius of 25 miles diistance. The NEVI formula wants to instal a charging stations every 50 miles.

Notice the gaps in California. The interesting and debatable part comes now. How should we define a Charger gap? and estimate where the extra revenue from Prop 30 funds should be deployed (keeping in mind NEVI formula funds will be deployed for the gaps).

The next map is where the grid substations are located across California. The general guidance is to install a station within 2-3 miles of a substation. (The light blue circles are a buffer zone of 3 miles from the substations.)

plot8 <- ggplot() +
